      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes": "adjust heat"
    },
    {
      "name": "low-sodium chicken broth",
      "amount": "1 cup",
      "notes": "hot"
    },
    {
      "name": "olive oil",
      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes": "for sauté"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium heat and brown the chicken cubes until lightly golden.",
    "Add minced garlic and onion, sauté until fragrant and translucent.",
    "Pour in soy sauce and vinegar, stir to combine, then add smoked paprika and crushed red pepper.",
    "Add the chicken broth, bring the mixture to a simmer, and let it cook for 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the grated comte cheese, allowing it to melt into the sauce and create a silky coating.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for an additional 5 minutes until the cheese is fully integrated.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste, then remove from heat.",
    "Serve hot over steamed rice or cauliflower rice for a low-carb option."
  ],
